snippet.title: Moon Patrol (Arcade) Playthrough Longplay Retro game
snippet.description: Moon Patrol (ムーンパトロール Mūn Patorōru) is an arcade game by Irem released in 1982. It was licensed to Williams for distribution in North America.[1] Moon Patrol is often credited for the introduction of parallax scrolling in side-scrolling video games. Taito's Jungle King side-scroller, released the same year as Moon Patrol, also uses parallax scrolling.
